star of the spot, it was (along with Bill Murray and the groundhog) the
perfect costar, and a crucial part of the ad. To that end, Lupinacci com-
mends Highdive, O PositiveFilms, and Jeep for delivering a great piece of
branded content “that did what every piece of branded content should do,
which is to focus on branded utility,” and demonstrating how a brand can
be useful or meaningful to a consumer’s life.
At the end of the day, this ad worked because it had a great hook.
Without the hook that the Super Bowl took place on Groundhog Day, and
that Bill Murray was the star of a movie about this subject as well as the
