Michael Breus, PhD, is known as “The Sleep Doctor,” which serves as his
Hook Point. It has helped him secure appearances on programs such as The
Dr. Oz Show more than 35 times, and on the Today show multiple times.
So how did Breus find this powerful Hook Point? Well, very early on in his
career, he became board certified in clinical sleep disorders. And while
there are terms for different types of doctors, such as pulmonologist for a
lung doctor or otolaryngologist for an ear, nose, and throat surgeon, there
was no term for doctors who deal with everything related to sleep.
In an attempt to find an effective way to market himself, Breus read a
book by Peter Montoya and Tim Vandehey called The Brand Called You. It
explained that your brand name should consist of what you do in three to
five words. Breus started asking people what they thought his occupation
was, and their answers always revolved around medicine and sleep. From
