based on how they perceive the world. In fact, many colleges and universi-
ties make comments about how well MUSE students communicate.
King believes that a lot of educational facilities do not prepare our youth
for the working world. Often the focus is on memorizing and regurgitating
information, but they aren’t shown how to communicate, manage stress, or
negotiate conflict, which is exactly what the PCM teaches them.
If a person is unaware of the PCM, they’re more likely to disengage
interviewers. For example, if an interviewer asks a question based in logic,
such as, “How long did you work for Apple?” and the interviewee’s pre-
ferred language is emotions, the person may respond with an emotional
