your biggest deals.
One time a friend of mine closed a deal worth tens of millions of dollars
that started with a cold outreach email. He did some research on LinkedIn
to find the key players at the company he wanted to target. When he found
the president of the department he wanted to reach, he figured out the
person’s email address by testing various email formats (a process described
later in this chapter). Once he found that email address, he sent a message
that said, “Hey, I have a couple of friends who’ve started a company. It
would be great to learn what you think about it because I’m considering
taking a job there.”

